sts; this reaction is a necessary speculative completion that uses alanine as an amino donor and reflects known biochemical logic where histidine emerges from imidazole-phosphate-rich intermediates. The gap is acknowledged and the network uses convergent prebiotic feedstocks to provide a plausible target-forming endpoint."}], "pathways": [{"pathway_id": "P1", "name": "Formate-acetate-pyruvate route", "description": "Classic hydrothermal carbon fixation feeds surface heterocycle and sugar chemistry, then converges biochemically to histidine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_004", "rxn_006", "rxn_008", "rxn_003", "rxn_009", "rxn_010", "rxn_011", "rxn_005", "rxn_012"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005", "mol_014", "mol_013", "mol_010", "mol_018"]}, {"pathway_id": "P2", "name": "Direct carbonyl-to-sugar branch", "description": "Hydrothermal carbonyl compounds directly seed sugar formation while separate nitrile chemistry supplies the imidazole branch.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_003", "rxn_009", "rxn_010", "rxn_006", "rxn_008", "rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_004", "rxn_011", "rxn_005", "rxn_012"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_008", "mol_010", "mol_013", "mol_014", "mol_018"]}, {"pathway_id": "P3", "name": "HCN-first convergent route", "description": "Surface HCN chemistry is established first, then hydrothermal pyruvate chemistry feeds the amino-acid side-chain component.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_006", "rxn_008", "rxn_003", "rxn_009", "rxn_010", "rxn_002", "rxn_004", "rxn_011", "rxn_005", "rxn_012"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_004", "mol_013", "mol_010", "mol_014", "mol_018"]}, {"pathway_id": "P4", "name": "Adenine-assisted nitrogen heterocycle route", "description": "HCN oligomerization to adenine accompanies the imidazole branch and represents an alternative nitrogen-rich surface chemistry context feeding the same late-stage assembly.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_008", "rxn_003", "rxn_009", "rxn_010", "rxn_002