nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Histidine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: The network targets histidine through convergent generation of four key hub classes: reduced C1/C2 feedstocks from hydrothermal CO2 fixation (formate, acetate), carbonyl/sugar intermediates from surface photochemistry and formose chemistry (formaldehyde, glycolaldehyde, ribose), nitrogen-rich heterocycle precursors from HCN chemistry (HCN, formamide, adenine, imidazole), and central metabolic keto-acid/amino-acid hubs from hydrothermal and biochemical transformations (pyruvate, alanine). The final target is reached by multiple prebiotically plausible but partly speculative biochemical couplings in which imidazole-derived nitrogen heterocycles, sugar/phosphate assemblies, and amino-acid side-chain precursors converge. Ten pathways are defined as distinct route combinations through the same connected bipartite network.\n\nMOLECULES (19 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formic acid/formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: C2H4O2 (acetate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C5H10O5 (ribose) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: CH3NO (formamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C5H5N5 (adenine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C3H3N2 (imidazole) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C3H7NO2 (alanine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: H3PO4 (phosphate) [starting]\n  - mol_017: C5H11NO7P (amino-ribose phosphate intermediate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_018: C8H14N2O7P (imidazole-ribose phosphate precursor) [intermediate]\n  - mol_019: C6H9N3O2 (histidine) [target]\n\nREACTIONS (12 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005 (Hydrothermal CO2 reduction to formate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_001, mol_002, mol_005 -> mol_006 (Hydrothermal acetate synthesis from CO2 and formate equivalents) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_007, mol_008 (Fischer-Tropsch-type formation of formaldehyde and glycolaldehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_001, mol_005, mol_006 -> mol_014 (Hydrothermal pyruvate synthesis from CO2 and acetate/formate feedstocks) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_005: mol_014, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_015 (Hydrothermal reductive amination of pyruvate to alanine) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_006: mol_005, mol_007, mol_003 -> mol_004, mol_011 (Surface photochemical generation of HCN and formamide from reduced carbon feedstocks) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_004 -> mol_012 (HCN oligomerization to adenine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_008: mol_011, mol_004 -> mol_013 (Formamide-based surface synthesis of imidazole-like heterocycle) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_007, mol_008 -> mol_009, mol_010 (Borate-stabilized formose chemistry to glyceraldehyde and ribose) [Surface]\n  - rxn_010: mol_010, mol_016, mol_003 -> mol_017 (Biochemical phosphorylation-amination of ribose to amino-ribose phosphate intermediate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_011: mol_013, mol_017, mol_014 -> mol_018 (Biochemical coupling of imidazole, amino-ribose phosphate, and pyruvate-derived side-chain precursor) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_012: mol_018, mol_015 -> mol_019 (Biochemical conversion of imidazole-ribose phosphate precursor to histidine) [Biochemical]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Formate-acetate-pyruvate route (11 steps)\n  - P2: Direct carbonyl-to-sugar branch (11 steps)\n  - P3: HCN-first convergent route (11 steps)\n  - P4: Adenine-assisted nitrogen heterocycle route (12 steps)\n  - P5: Alanine-donor late transamination route (11 steps)\n  - P6: Formamide-driven heterocycle route (10 steps)\n  - P7: Carbonyl-rich hydrothermal