", "description": "CO2 is reduced to formate, extended to acetate and pyruvate, then merged with the HCN-derived imidazole branch and finished by transamination.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_005", "rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_009", "rxn_010", "rxn_011", "rxn_012"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005", "mol_011", "mol_013", "mol_014", "mol_015"]}, {"pathway_id": "P2", "name": "Formaldehyde-first sugar-assisted histidine route", "description": "Hydrothermal formaldehyde feeds surface sugar chemistry, generating glycolaldehyde before cyanosulfidic access to aminoimidazole and late-stage histidine assembly.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_007", "rxn_009", "rxn_010", "rxn_004", "rxn_005", "rxn_011", "rxn_012"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_007", "mol_008", "mol_013", "mol_011", "mol_015"]}, {"pathway_id": "P3", "name": "Ribose-associated heterocycle pathway", "description": "Formaldehyde enters borate-stabilized sugar chemistry through glycolaldehyde and glyceraldehyde to ribose, while the same carbonyl pool supports aminoimidazole generation before convergence onto the histidine precursor.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_002", "rxn_007", "rxn_008", "rxn_009", "rxn_010", "rxn_004", "rxn_011", "rxn_012"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_008", "mol_009", "mol_010", "mol_014", "mol_015"]}, {"pathway_id": "P4", "name": "Pyruvate-first transamination route", "description": "Hydrothermal chemistry prioritizes pyruvate and alanine formation, then a separately generated imidazole aldehyde side-chain precursor is attached and aminated.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_001", "rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_005", "rxn_006", "rxn_009", "rxn_010", "rxn_011", "rxn_012"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_011", "mol_012", "mol_013", "mol_014", "mol_015"]}, {"pathway_id": "P5", "name": "Formamide-rich heterocycle route", "description": "A surface HCN/formamide reservoir is used to reach imidazole-4-carboxaldehyde, which then condenses with hydrothermal pyr